{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Normal}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/GO|species=Herdier}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Normal|prevnum=506|prev=Lillipup|nextnum=508|next=Stoutland|roundleft=bl|roundright=br}}\n|}\n{{Pokémon Infobox\n|name=Herdier\n|jname=ハーデリア\n|jtranslit=Hāderia\n|tmname=Herderrie\n|category=Loyal Dog\n|typebox=1\n|type1=Normal\n|abilityn=d\n|ability1=Intimidate\n|ability2=Sand Rush\n|abilityd=Scrappy\n|ndex=507\n|udex=013\n|u2dex=023\n|adex=121\n|height-ftin=2\'11"\n|height-m=0.9\n|weight-lbs=32.4\n|weight-kg=14.7\n|egggroupn=1\n|egggroup1=Field\n|eggcycles=15\n|expyield=130\n|lv100exp=1,059,860\n|gendercode=127\n|color=Gray\n|catchrate=120\n|evtotal=2\n|evat=2\n|body=08\n|pokefordex=herdier\n|generation=5\n|friendship=70\n}}\n\'\'\'Herdier\'\'\' ([[List of Japanese Pokémon names|Japanese]]: \'\'\'ハーデリア\'\'\' \'\'Herderrie\'\') is a {{type|Normal}} {{OBP|Pokémon|species}} introduced in [[Generation V]].\n\nIt [[evolution|evolves]] from {{p|Lillipup}} starting at [[level]] 16 and evolves into {{p|Stoutland}} starting at level 32.\n\n==Biology==\nHerdier is a light brown, canine Pokémon with a short snout. Its face has long, cream fur, which forms a mustache and a three-pointed crest. Its ears are large and perked, and it has a black nose. It has shaggy dark blue fur covering its body and short tail. This hard, thick fur serves to protect Herdier from attacks. It has four short legs, with three-toed paws. Each paw has a dark blue paw pad that can be seen in [[Pokédex 3D Pro]]. Herdier is very loyal, and it will help its {{pkmn|Trainer}} raise other Pokémon. It has helped Trainers since long ago.\n\n==In the anime==\n===In the main series===\n[[File:Lusamine Herdier.png|thumb|left|250px|Herdier in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\n====Major appearances====\nHerdier debuted in \'\'[[BW016|Rematch at the Nacrene Gym!]]\'\', under the ownership of [[Lenora]]. It battled against {{Ash}} and his {{AP|Tepig}} during a [[Gym]] {{pkmn|battle}}, but it was eventually defeated by Tepig\'s {{m|Flame Charge}}.It reappeared in a flashback in \'\'[[BW103|Certain Up, Unova League!]]\'\'.\n\nTwo Herdier appeared in \'\'[[BW022|A Venipede Stampede!]]\'\', under the ownership of the [[Officer Jenny]] in [[Castelia City]]. They were used during an effort to curb the tide of invading {{p|Venipede}}.\n\nA Herdier appeared in \'\'[[BW111|There\'s a New Gym Leader in Town!]]\'\', under the ownership of [[Cheren]]. It defeated [[Ash\'s Oshawott]] with {{m|Thunder Fang}} during an unofficial battle.\n\nA Herdier appeared in \'\'[[SM046|Deceiving Appearances!]]\'\', under the ownership of {{an|Lusamine}}. She keeps it as company in her office at the [[Aether Paradise]] mansion. Herdier reappeared in a flashback in \'\'[[SM049|Mission: Total Recall!]]\'\'.\n\n====Minor appearances====\nA Herdier appeared in [[Trip]]\'s flashback in \'\'[[BW031|Ash and Trip\'s Third Battle!]]\'\', where he remembered it being defeated by [[Alder]]\'s {{p|Bouffalant}}.\n\nA Herdier appeared in a flashback in [[M14|\'\'White—Victini and Zekrom\'\' and \'\'Black—Victini and Reshiram\'\']].\n\nA Herdier appeared in \'\'[[BW052|Ash Versus the Champion!]]\'\', under the ownership of another Officer Jenny.\n\nA {{pkmn|Trainer}}\'s Herdier made a cameo appearance in \'\'[[BW067|Cilan Takes Flight]]\'\'.\n\nA Trainer\'s Herdier made a cameo appearance in \'\'[[BW069|Climbing the Tower of Success!]]\'\'.\n\nA Herdier appeared in \'\'[[M15|Kyurem VS. The Sword of Justice]]\'\', under the ownership of {{un|Kanata}}. It was seen battling and losing against [[Misaki]]\'s {{p|Liepard}} in the [[Roshan City]] [[Pokémon Center]]. Another Herdier appeared during the {{OBP|Swords of Justice|M15}} legend.\n\nA Trainer\'s Herdier appeared in \'\'[[BW103|Curtain Up, Unova League!]]\'\'.\n\nA Trainer\'s Herdier appeared in \'\'[[BW112|Team Plasma\'s Pokémon Power Plot!]]\'\'. Another Herdier appeared in a flashback in the same episode.\n\nA Herdier appeared in \'\'[[M16|Genesect and the Legend Awakened]]\'\' as a resident of [[Pokémon Hills]].\n\nA Trainer\'s Herdier appeared in \'\'[[XY057|Thawing an Icy Panic!]]\'\'.\n\nTwo Trainers\' Herdier appeared in \'\'[[SM001|Alola to New Adventure!]]\'\'.\n\nA Trainer\'s Herdier appeared in \'\'[[SM006|A Shocking Grocery Run!]]\'\'.\n\nA Herdier appeared in \'\'[[SM011|Young Kiawe Had a Farm!]]\'\' at [[Paniola Ranch]], which is owned by {{an|Kiawe}}\'s family. It was used by the family to herd all of the ranch\'s Pokémon. It appeared again in \'\'[[SM070|The Young Flame Strikes Back!]]\'\', where it barked at [[Viren]] and his {{p|Electivire}} as they arrived at Paniola Ranch.\n\nA Trainer\'s Herdier appeared in \'\'[[SM013|Racing to a Big Event!]]\'\', where it participated in the [[Pokémon Pancake Race]].\n\nTwo Trainers\' Herdier appeared in \'\'[[SM017|Crystal-Clear Sleuthing!]]\'\'.\n\nTwo Trainers\' Herdier appeared in \'\'[[SM021|One Journey Ends, Another Begins...]]\'\'\n\nA Trainer\'s Herdier appeared in \'\'[[SM023|Getting the Band Back Together!]]\'\'.\n\nA Trainer\'s Herdier appeared in \'\'[[SM027|A Glaring Rivalry!]]\'\'.\n\nA Herdier appeared in \'\'[[SM032|Treasure Hunt, Akala Style!]]\'\'.\n\nA Trainer\'s Herdier appeared in \'\'[[SM050|Faba\'s Revenge!]]\'\'.\n\nA Trainer\'s Herdier appeared in \'\'[[SM068|Real Life...Inquire Within!]]\'\'.\n\nA Trainer\'s Herdier appeared in \'\'[[SM072|Sours for the Sweet!]]\'\'.\n\nA Herdier appeared in \'\'[[SM096|Don\'t Ignore the Small Stufful!]]\'\' as one of the Pokémon staying at [[Aether Paradise]].\n\nA Trainer\'s Herdier appeared in \'\'[[SM099|We Know Where You\'re Going, Eevee!]]\'\'.\n\nA Trainer\'s Herdier appeared in \'\'[[SM129|Battle Royal 151!]]\'\', where it competed in the [[Battle Royal]] preliminary round of the [[Manalo Conference]] but was defeated by [[Sandy]] and {{DL|Recurring wild Pokémon in the anime|Shaymin}}.\n\nTwo Trainers\' Herdier appeared in \'\'[[SM133|Battling on the Wing!]]\'\'. One was watching the {{pkmn|battle}}s during the Manalo Conference, while the other was waiting in line with its Trainer for {{TRT}}\'s food truck.\n\nA Trainer\'s Herdier appeared in [[SM141]].\n\n====Pokédex entries====\n{{Animedexheader|Unova}}\n{{Animedexbody|BW016|Herdier|Ash\'s Pokédex|Herdier, the Loyal Dog Pokémon, and the evolved form of Lillipup. Herdier\'s hard black fur softens its opponent\'s attacks like armor.}}\n{{Animedexbody|BW111|Herdier|Ash\'s Pokédex|Herdier, the Loyal Dog Pokémon and the evolved form of Lillipup. Always obedient and faithful to their Trainers, Herdier have helped them raise other Pokémon since long ago.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'Black & White\'\'|Unova}}\n\n===In Pokémon Generations===\n[[File:Lenora Herdier PG.png|thumb|250px|Herdier in [[Pokémon Generations]]]]\n[[Lenora]]\'s Herdier appeared in \'\'[[PG13|The Uprising]]\'\'.\n{{-}}\n\n==In the manga==\n[[File:Lenora Lillipup Herdier Adventures.png|thumb|Herdier (middle) in [[Pokémon Adventures]]]]\n===In the [[Pokémon Adventures]] manga===\nIn \'\'[[PS462|Choices]]\'\', the man who delivers [[Professor Juniper]]\'s package to {{adv|Black}} owns a Herdier.\n\nA {{pkmn|Trainer}}\'s Herdier appeared in \'\'[[PS466|An Odd Speech]]\'\'.\n\n[[Lenora]] has a {{p|Stoutland}}, which she has owned since it was a Lillipup. It was seen in a flashback in \'\'[[PS474|Defeating Stoutland]]\'\'.\n\nA Herdier appeared in \'\'[[PS483|Special Delivery]]\'\' as one of the Pokémon competing in {{ci|Nimbasa}}\'s [[Pokémon Musical]].\n\nA Herdier appeared in a flashback in \'\'[[PS510|A Wretched Reunion]]\'\', under the ownership of a mailman.\n\nA Trainer\'s Herdier appeared in \'\'[[PS513|Into the Quarterfinals!]]\'\'.\n\n==In the TCG==\n{{main|Herdier (TCG)}}\n\n==Game data==\n===NPC appearances===\n* {{g|Mystery Dungeon: Gates to Infinity}}: Herdier is a minor character of the game and a resident of [[Post Town]].\n\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Dex/Header|type=Normal}}\n